<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/180401AHTPKTMBJLKQPMDKQDCPGMTLVJT> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "CVIFF 2026 Opening Night - The Art of Adventure";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">The Art of Adventure</span> <span><br/></span>(CVIFF 2026 Opening Night Feature)  <span><br/></span>2025, Canada, 86 minutes, English, Documentary<span><br/></span>Directed by: Alison Reid<span><br/></span>Cast: Robert Bateman, Bristol Foster, David Suzuki, Wade Davis, Guujaaw, Briony Penn, Tara Cullis <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">The Art of Adventure</span><span><br/></span>In 1957, renowned wildlife artist Robert Bateman and fearless biologist Bristol Foster were a pair of young men, finding their way.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Looking for adventure – and meaning – the two set off on a 30,000 kilometre trek that would change both of their lives.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Driving their beloved Land Rover – The Grizzly Torque – through Africa, India, and beyond, they came back with experiences that would shape their careers.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Combining home movies taken during the trip, and drawings and paintings made along the way – with commentary by Bateman and Foster – <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Art of Adventure</span> is a unique look at how this trip of a lifetime was deeply influential on both men.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The Art Of Adventure recently won the Mountain Culture Film Award at the Whistler Film Festival and was named the 2026 Feature Film Festival Winner at the Reel Canadian Film Fest.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Stay afterwards for a Q&A with the filmmakers!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">This film is unrated.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">About CVIFF</span> <span><br/></span>The Comox Valley International Film Festival (CVIFF) is a non-profit organization that discovers and supports independent films from around the world and introduces them to audiences. We believe in the power of a good story! <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://cviff.ca/\"> cviff.ca</a><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-04-02T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/files/9bc24644-857a-41cb-a33d-ce5c5902a709.jpg>;
