<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/169801ADKHSPCDPNCSVSLSBGGVRMRGSPC> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Children by Lucy Kirkwood ";
  schema:description """
	Directed by Catherine Hannon<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>After a major disaster at a nuclear power plant, Hazel and Robin, nuclear engineers, have retreated to their remote coastal cottage, seeking to re-establish some kind of normal life. Out of the blue, Rose, a fellow scientist whom they haven’t seen for years, turns up. Has she come to rekindle old relationships or is she hiding some darker motive? <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"Sly, gripping, darkly funny...This is sci-fi kitted out with real people, real dilemmas, real scope.\" --The Times<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"Grips compulsively...Genuinely disturbing...Leaves you an abundance of ideas on which to ruminate.\" --Guardian<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Nominated for Tony Award for Best Play, winner of U.K. Writer's Guild Award for Best New Play. In 2019, writers for The Guardian placed <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Children</span> third on a list of the greatest theatrical works since 2000.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Tickets for April 17 performance include an opportunity to attend an informal discussion after the show with the cast and director.</span></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-04-15T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
