<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/165201AGGSVDBPDRVDGKMLBKRTNVRNSQG> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Golden Anniversaries";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">By Mark Crawford</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">An Arts Club Theatre Company production</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">TWO PEOPLE, ONE COTTAGE, FIFTY YEARS</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Since they got married, Glen and Sandy Golden have celebrated every wedding anniversary by coming to the same cottage for a romantic getaway. This weekend marks a major milestone: 50 years of wedded bliss. Well, mostly bliss....A week ago, Sandy cancelled their big anniversary party and kicked Glen to the curb. Now, he wants to talk. Join the Goldens as they recount the good, the bad, and the ugly of spending half a century together. From the writer of <span class=\"ItalicText\">Bed and Breakfast</span> and <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Birds and the Bees</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Golden Anniversaries</span> is a funny, tender comedy-drama about the kind of love that endures - even when it’s tested by time, change, and the realities of growing older together.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Comedy that strikes a deep chord” - The Kincardine Record</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">CREDITS</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Cast<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Peter Anderson</span> Glen<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Eileen Barrett</span> Sandy<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Creative<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Arthi Chandra</span> Director<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ryan Cormack</span> Set Designer<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Madeleine Polak</span> Costume Designer<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Alexandra Caprara</span> Lighting Designer<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Rick Colhoun</span> Sound Designer<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Lisa Goebel</span> Intimacy Director<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ronaye Haynes</span> Intimacy Captain<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ronaye Haynes</span> Stage Manager<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Emma Graveson</span> Apprentice Stage Manager<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Mark Crawford is a member of the Playwright's Guild of Canada<span><br/></span>Produced by permission of Playwright & Marquis Literary (Colin Rivers) www.MQlit.ca
""";
